This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action detection in videos using 3D Convolutional Neural Networks. It also involves image processing and analysis. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses deep learning techniques to train the model. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with video data and involves processing and analyzing multiple streams of data. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves developing a model that can detect actions in videos, which is a task that requires intelligence. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves training a neural network to detect actions in videos.
